android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT.info: necessary for connecting to paired Bluetooth devices.
android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT.description: Required to be able to connect to paired Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.CALL_PHONE.description: Allows the application to call phone numbers without your intervention. Malicious applications may cause unexpected calls on your phone bill. Note that this does not allow the application to call emergency numbers.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.READ_CONTACTS.description: Allows an application to read all of the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your data to other people.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS.description: Allows access to the list of accounts in the Accounts Service.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Allows an application to receive push notifications from cloud.

android.permission.SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM.info: permits exact alarm scheduling for background work.
android.permission.SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM.description: Allows an app to use exact alarm scheduling APIs to perform timing sensitive background work.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES.info: allows reading image files from external storage.
android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES.description: Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS.info: allows an app to post notifications.
android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS.description: Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.USE_EXACT_ALARM.info: allows using exact alarms without user permission.
android.permission.USE_EXACT_ALARM.description: Allows apps to use exact alarms just like with SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM but without needing to request this permission from the user. This is only intended for use by apps that rely on exact alarms for their core functionality. You should continue using SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM if your app needs exact alarms for a secondary feature that users may or may not use within your app.  Keep in mind that this is a powerful permission and app stores may enforce policies to audit and review the use of this permission. Such audits may involve removal from the app store if the app is found to be misusing this permission.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.info: allow app to access the device's advertising ID.
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.description: This ID is a unique, user-resettable identifier provided by Google's advertising services, allowing apps to track user behavior for advertising purposes while maintaining user privacy.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.info: enables regular apps to use Service.startForeground.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground.

metadata.cwe: CWE-532: Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File
metadata.description: The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.

metadata.cwe: CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')
metadata.description: App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.
App can read/write to External Storage. Any App can read data written to External Storage.

metadata.cwe: CWE-749: Exposed Dangerous Method or Function
metadata.description: Insecure WebView Implementation. Execution of user controlled code in WebView is a critical Security Hole.
Ensure that user controlled URLs never reaches the Webview. Enabling file access from URLs in WebView can leak sensitive information from the file system.

metadata.cwe: CWE-327: Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: Calling Cipher.getInstance("AES") will return AES ECB mode by default. ECB mode is known to be weak as it results in the same ciphertext for identical blocks of plaintext.

metadata.cwe: CWE-330: Use of Insufficiently Random Values
metadata.description: The App uses an insecure Random Number Generator.

metadata.cwe: CWE-312: Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive information like usernames, passwords, keys etc.
App creates temp file. Sensitive information should never be written into a temp file.
IP Address disclosure
This App may have root detection capabilities.

metadata.cwe: CWE-327: Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: SHA-1 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.
The file or SharedPreference is World Readable. Any App can read from the file

metadata.cwe: CWE-649: Reliance on Obfuscation or Encryption of Security-Relevant Inputs without Integrity Checking
metadata.description: The App uses the encryption mode CBC with PKCS5/PKCS7 padding. This configuration is vulnerable to padding oracle attacks.

"helpfaq43a" : "The CONTOUR™DIABETES app can notify you if certain trends are detected in your blood sugar readings. The group of blood sugar readings that make up a trend is called a ‘Pattern’. For example, the app may detect a pattern of high blood sugars at lunchtime or lows on Tuesdays.

The Patterns feature lets you:

"imbfrequencyprecautions1" : "1. Avoid the pads of your fingers. You might want to use the sides of your fingertips, which are less sensitive than other parts of your fingers.

2. Avoid cold hands. To minimize discomfort when testing, wash your hands in warm water to increase the circulation in your fingers.

3. Change the puncture depth. Most lancing devices have a depth adjuster, so you might try a lower setting.

4. Use soap and water. Instead of cleaning your finger with an alcohol wipe, wash your hands with soaps and water instead. Alcohol tightens the skin and makes it harder to get a blood drop.

5. Alternate fingers. Be sure to alternate fingers instead of using the same one or two fingers to test.

6. Test with a new lance. Since lancets may get dull with each use, be sure to change it every time you test.

7. Consider Alternate Site Testing. Ask your healthcare professional about alternate site testing. Using your palm, your arm, or another part of your body may be an option for you when you are not concerned about your blood sugar trending low."

"imbfrequencyprecautions2" : "1. Practice deep breathing. Inhale for 4 seconds; hold your breath for another 4 seconds; then slowly exhale for 4 seconds. Repeat this several time to relax your body.

2. Admit that you feel anxious. Anxiety is just one of many emotions people feel. Although feeling anxious is not pleasant, it is what you feel at the moment and you will be able to tolerate it.

3. Question what you are thinking. When people are anxious, they tend to start thinking about many highly unrealistic things that could happen - and that only makes anxiety worse. Remember to ask yourself questions like \"Is it realistic to worry about this?\" or \"Is my perception really accurate or does it just seem this way?\"

4. Visualize something calming. Imagine you are beside a stream or in a field, watching leaves floating by on the water or clouds passing in the sky. When you feel anxious, let your thoughts and emotions float downstream on those leaves or float by on the clouds.

5. Give yourself positive advice. Anxiety can create a lot of negative thoughts. When you feel anxious, tell yourself \"I know this anxiety doesn\'t feel good, but I can find ways to cope with it\".

6. Stay focused on getting things done. Avoid being passive and obsessing about how you feel, even though you are anxious. Focus on the things that you were planning to do, and do them."

playstore_details.title: CONTOUR DIABETES app (US)
playstore_details.description:
The easy-to-use CONTOUR™DIABETES app is designed for adults of all ages with diabetes.(1) Since 2016, there have been over 1.2 million downloads.(2) Start your download and enjoy your journey.

People using the system say they:(1,3)
•	better understood their diabetes
•	significantly decreased HbA1c values
•	didn't find it to be a hassle that compromised their quality of life

The CONTOUR™DIABETES app syncs with a CONTOUR™ connected meter for seamless blood glucose monitoring. This easy-to-use app can give you a better understanding of how your daily activities affect your blood glucose results to help you manage your diabetes. In addition to using the CONTOUR™DIABETES app, always consult with your Health Care Professional before making any changes to your diet, exercise or treatment regimen.

The CONTOUR™DIABETES app presents your blood glucose results in a simple and easy-to-review way that’s personalized to you. Download the CONTOUR™DIABETES app today and start receiving meaningful information on your progress, with some of the latest features...
•	My Patterns – can notify you of trends in your blood glucose readings, by presenting you with potential causes and guidance on how you may improve
•	Test Reminder Plans – let you optimize your testing regime to give you results that are more insightful
•	Record – allows you to record events such as diet, activities and medication, and also add photos, notes or voice memos to help put your results in context
•	View – if you use insulin and/or log your carbs, you can now see your insulin doses, carb intakes and blood glucose results in one simple view
•	Share – give your healthcare professional greater insight with the easy-to-read diary report – send this report in advance or take it with you on the day of your appointment
•	Apple Health™ - is now integrated with the CONTOUR™DIABETES app

Learn more about the CONTOUR™DIABETES app and CONTOUR™ connected meters at:
www.diabetes.ascensia.com
compatibility.contourone.com

Note: Screenshots are for illustration purposes. Availability of blood glucose meter model based on country of purchase. Units of measurement in the app will match that of your synced meter. For more information, please refer to the user guide for your CONTOUR™ connected meter.

© 2021 Ascensia Diabetes Care Holdings AG. All rights reserved.

Manufacturer
Ascensia Diabetes Care Holdings AG
5 Wood Hollow Rd.
Parsippany, NJ 07054
www.contourone.com

Ascensia, the Ascensia Diabetes Care logo and Contour are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Ascensia Diabetes Care Holdings AG.

1.	Fisher W et al. User Experience with a New Smartphone Application for Blood Glucose Monitoring (BGM) in an Information-Motivation-Behavioral Skills (IMB) Model Study. Poster presented at the 12th International Conference on Advanced Technologies & Treatments For Diabetes (ATTD); February 20-23, 2019; Berlin, Germany.
2.	Data on file. Ascensia Diabetes Care. DCAM-147-5682.
3.	Fernandez-Garcia D et al. The ICONE Study: A multicenter evaluation of the impact of CONTOUR™NEXT ONE and CONTOUR™DIABETES app on Self-Management and Adherence in Insulin-Treated Patients with Diabetes. ePoster presented at European Endocrinology Society Congress (ECE), 5-9 September 2020.

hotspot.title: Found 13 critical permission(s)
hotspot.description:
Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read/modify/delete external storage contents - Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_SCAN (dangerous): required for discovering and pairing Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to discover and pair nearby Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADVERTISE (dangerous): required to advertise to nearby Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to advertise to nearby Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT (dangerous): necessary for connecting to paired Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to connect to paired Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.CAMERA (dangerous): take pictures and videos - Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE (dangerous): read phone state and identity - Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.CALL_PHONE (dangerous): directly call phone numbers - Allows the application to call phone numbers without your intervention. Malicious applications may cause unexpected calls on your phone bill. Note that this does not allow the application to call emergency numbers.

android.permission.READ_CONTACTS (dangerous): read contact data - Allows an application to read all of the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your data to other people.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION (dangerous): fine (GPS) location - Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION (dangerous): coarse (network-based) location - Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS (dangerous): list accounts - Allows access to the list of accounts in the Accounts Service.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES (dangerous): allows reading image files from external storage. - Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS (dangerous): allows an app to post notifications. - Allows an app to post notifications
